{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, ensuring that ML-based WCET estimates complement existing development and verification processes is crucial for their adoption and utility.",
    "RL methods inherently adapt and improve their strategies based on feedback from the environment, which allows for more extensive exploration and exploitation of the solution space.",
    "This adaptability leads to WCET estimations without the extensive need for labeled data, which is often a critical requirement in ML approaches.",
    "Consequently, RL would offer a more flexible mechanism for WCET estimation in complex real-time systems.",
    "This comparison is anchored against a baseline provided by a random algorithm, before delving into a direct comparison between the two primary algorithms under study."
  ]
}